Chainer Discard mono black control:
 - Abhorrent overlord (combo piece but meh otherwise, i almost never win that way)
 - Karn Liberated (covers some blind spots in mono black but almost no synergy with the rest of the deck)
 + Bolas's Citadel (seems good)
 + Command the Dreadhorde (curious to see if this is any good, might be redundant on top of chainer)

Red Grenzo Goblins:
 - Dark-Dweller Oracle (i never want to sac my dudes because of Grenzo triggers)
 + New Krenko (does a lot of what i want -- more tokens)

Nic Mizzet Parun Counterburn
 - Memory Lapse (i think i play too many counterspells, going to remove from what i htink might be worst)
 - Merfolk Looter (i always like opening my hand with this card but late game its worthless)
 + Narsets Reversal (seems like a really good card, have to fit it in somehow)
 + Firemind Vessel (curves out nicely with niv mizzet, letting me have a mana open after i cast him the turn after, brings me 2 turns closer. There aren't many rocks that tap for two colored)

Didn't make the cut:
 - Role Reversal, was cool because its sorcery speed, but unfortunately i don't have very many creatures i want to give away.
 - Spark Double, seems really good with Niv Mizzet... but.... ehhhhh...... seems like a little winmore

Zegana Big Sea Creatures
 - Stunt Double (playing too many clones i think, this seemed like the worst one. being instant speed doesn't give me much)
 - Progenitor Mimic (the most expensive cmc of all the clones. I don't really need mroe copies either i dont think)
 + Spark Double (seems better than the previous two for Zegana, also I have a bunch of legendary seadudes)
 + Awakening of Vitu-Ghazi (9/9 for 5 mana seems fine, and activates Zegana for a bunch the turn after. Not really in theme but i can put it on an island!)
thats all folks, let me know what you think
